{"layout": {"_meta": {"importer": "lg-legacy-import 0.1.0", "imported_at": "2026-05-22T14:37:31+00:00", "imported_from": 1234, "original_title": "Dying / Aging Plastic Parts", "unhandled_meta": ["marked_patron_only"]}, "blocks": [{"id": "b_e5e16fbe", "tier": "", "type": "post-header", "title": "Dying / Aging Plastic Parts", "tagline": "Here is a method I use frequently to dye plastic using RIT synthetic fabric dyes, acetone, and water. &nbsp; Mix approximately 25% acetone with 75% water and gradually add the RIT\u2026", "show_tags": true, "show_byline": true, "show_categories": true, "featured_image_id": 1237}, {"id": "b_4f6d1f6", "html": "<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\nHere is a method I use frequently to dye plastic using RIT synthetic fabric dyes, acetone, and water.\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1238,\"width\":616,\"height\":462,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img class=\"wp-image-1238\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_5378-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"616\" height=\"462\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\nMix approximately 25% acetone with 75% water and gradually add the RIT dye to achieve the desired color. The acetone allows the dye to \"bite\" into the plastic while the water dilutes the effect so it doesn't act too aggressively. I just eyeball the measurements and test frequently on scrap material until I am happy with the results. The majority of the time I use a combination of Chocolate Brown and Daffodil Yellow. (And while the RIT dyes are my base, in the example below I used a little GluBoost red to get my final color).\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":1236,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img class=\"wp-image-1236\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3885-2-1-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1237,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img class=\"wp-image-1237\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\nFor small parts like knobs or tuner buttons I make enough to submerge the parts. For larger items I wipe it on and then off with a paper towel working quickly to achieve an even color. It's a good idea to start with a weak mixture and work up to the final color.\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1240,\"width\":758,\"height\":569,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img class=\"wp-image-1240\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_4982-2-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":1241,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img class=\"wp-image-1241\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-3-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":1242,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img class=\"wp-image-1242\" src=\"https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_4187-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\r\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->", "type": "wysiwyg"}, {"id": "b_313ecb62", "type": "post-footer", "show_author": true, "show_related": false}], "schema": 1}, "post_context": {"date": "June 17, 2023", "media": {"1237": {"id": 1237, "alt": "", "url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2.jpg", "mime": "image/jpeg", "sizes": {"large": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-1024x1024.jpg", "width": 1024, "height": 1024}, "medium": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-300x300.jpg", "width": 300, "height": 300}, "1536x1536": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-1536x1536.jpg", "width": 1536, "height": 1536}, "thumbnail": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-150x150.jpg", "width": 150, "height": 150}, "exs-square": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-800x800.jpg", "width": 800, "height": 800}, "medium_large": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-768x768.jpg", "width": 768, "height": 768}, "d4p-bbp-thumb": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-128x72.jpg", "width": 128, "height": 72}, "post-thumbnail": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-855x855.jpg", "width": 855, "height": 855}, "exs-square-half": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-800x400.jpg", "width": 800, "height": 400}, "woocommerce_single": {"url": "https://dev.loothgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/IMG_3889-2-600x600.jpg", "width": 600, "height": 600}, "woocommerce_thum